topics.body:
I just realized something; people in the usa born from 1990-2005 are probably going to be completely forgotten in the long scheme of things because, not to sound like a ass, but those that are already adults have accomplished very little versus older generations back when they were younger.

Not to mention that looking at congress the average age is 55; the people that are extremely old are already being replaced by people in their 30's or they're going to retire in another decade or two meaning a disproportionately low numbers of people currently reaching adulthood being represented.


To put it simply: on average people born from 1990 to 2005 are the embodiment of failures and probably won't matter at all in the long run both achievement wise or politically cause on average they don't have the skills to succeed in a technological industry nor are there any job openings available for them; thus they're forever doomed to be chronically unemployed and such.


Tl:dr; people born in the usa from 1990-2005 don't have the skills to survive with how the usa is becoming a technological industry so chances are they're fucked.

"@HJSDGCE":/dis/the-time-wasting-thread/post/5525d3126368725fa3120000#post_5525d3126368725fa3120000
Are you a skilled laborer?

The usa is shifting drastically to a technology industry; to put it simply: If you want to succeed with the way the economy is going you need to become a skilled laborer.


If you want to succeed now you *HAVE* to become a skilled laborer; it doesn't matter if it's being a carpenter, welder, programmer, doctor or such you *HAVE* to become a skilled laborer.  To make it as blunt as humanly possible 70% of low income jobs are going to be automated within ten years; if you don't have any higher skills or such you're going to have a bad time because if you're hoping to live off working at mcdonalds or walmart you won't be able to because all those jobs will be eliminated entirely.

Tl:dr; earn a useful college degree cause 70% of low income jobs are going to be eliminated in the next ten years.
